  },
  {
    "chunk_id": "docling_jiaocai_jiaocai_en_310_3",
    "text": "Zhejiang University Theory of Computation, Fall-Winter 2015 Final Exam",
    "canon_role": "section_header",
    "bbox": [
      0.28952772222836737,
      0.33134920599050016,
      0.7043121148968894,
      0.3808139534887723
    ],
    "page": "jiaocai_jiaocai_en_310",
    "order": 5
  },
  {
    "chunk_id": "docling_jiaocai_jiaocai_en_310_4",
    "text": "(20%) Determine whether the following statements are true or false. If it is true write a O otherwise a x in the bracket before the statement.",
    "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
    "bbox": [
      0.13141685727614386,
      0.3997093032741303,
      0.8767966757149586,
      0.4317956347663967
    ],
    "page": "jiaocai_jiaocai_en_310",
    "order": 6
  },
  {
    "chunk_id": "docling_jiaocai_jiaocai_en_310_5",
    "text": "(a) ( ) Let L be any regular language. Then the number of equivalence classes respect to language L (i.e. x ~L y, if for all z € L*, xz E L iff yz E L) is finite.",
    "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
    "bbox": [
      0.1622176696497189,
      0.44186046525362854,
      0.876796721644325,
      0.47529069735538304
    ],
    "page": "jiaocai_jiaocai_en_310",
    "order": 7
  },
  {
    "chunk_id": "docling_jiaocai_jiaocai_en_310_6",
    "text": "(b) ( ) The language {a\"\"w/wE {a, b}* *, nE N, and |w| = 2n} is context-free.",
    "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
    "bbox": [
      0.1601642846063008,
      0.48401162747943,
      0.8583162178167605,
      0.5000000002494945
    ],
    "page": "jiaocai_jiaocai_en_310",
    "order": 8
  },
  {
    "chunk_id": "docling_jiaocai_jiaocai_en_310_7",
    "text": "(c) ( ) The language {\"M\" \"w\" |M accepts w in less than 2016 steps } is not recursive.",
    "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
    "bbox": [
      0.16016427894561908,
      0.5071924598620758,
      0.874743300725839,
      0.539349388930071
    ],
    "page": "jiaocai_jiaocai_en_310",
    "order": 9
  },
  {
    "chunk_id": "docling_jiaocai_jiaocai_en_310_8",
    "text": "(d) ( ) The language {\"M\" | M is a TM and L(M) is Context-free but L(M) is not regular, is not recursive.",
    "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
    "bbox": [
      0.15811088203063114,
      0.5493551586268136,
      0.8747433130823054,
      0.5828488372351387
    ],
    "page": "jiaocai_jiaocai_en_310",
    "order": 10
  },
  {
    "chunk_id": "docling_jiaocai_jiaocai_en_310_9",
    "text": "(e) ( ) The language {\"M\" \"M,\" | M, and Me are TMs, and M, halts on e but Ma doesn't halt on e} is recursively enumerable, but not recursive.",
    "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
    "bbox": [
      0.1601642917279597,
      0.5915178572250318,
      0.8747433135081795,
      0.6264880952639315
    ],
    "page": "jiaocai_jiaocai_en_310",
    "order": 11
  },
  {
    "chunk_id": "docling_jiaocai_jiaocai_en_310_10",
    "text": "(f) ( ) The set of all primitive recursive functions is a proper subset of the set of all u-recursive functions.",
    "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
    "bbox": [
      0.1642710579182321,
      0.6351686506891945,
      0.8747433039571959,
      0.6656976744480745
    ],
    "page": "jiaocai_jiaocai_en_310",
    "order": 12
  },
  {
    "chunk_id": "docling_jiaocai_jiaocai_en_310_11",
    "text": "(g) ( ) Let A and B be two disjoint recursively enumerable languages. If AU B is also be recursively enumerable, then it is possible that neither A nor B is decidable.",
    "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
    "bbox": [
      0.1601642831661461,
      0.674355158269708,
      0.8747971117257376,
      0.727133996785131
    ],
    "page": "jiaocai_jiaocai_en_310",
    "order": 13
  },
  {
    "chunk_id": "docling_jiaocai_jiaocai_en_310_12",
    "text": "(h) ( ) Let H10 = {\"M\" |M is a TM and 10 € L(M)} and 1 and 2 are recursive functions. If H10 Sm L and H1o Sm L, then L is recursive enumerable but not recursive.",
    "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
    "bbox": [
      0.16016429388401707,
      0.7353670636440793,
      0.8747433206689664,
      0.7848837207188762
    ],
    "page": "jiaocai_jiaocai_en_310",
    "order": 14
  },
  {
    "chunk_id": "docling_jiaocai_jiaocai_en_310_13",
    "text": "(i) ( ) Suppose SAT ≤p L and L € P. Then P = NP.",
    "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
    "bbox": [
      0.16427106837655878,
      0.7965116282260124,
      0.6468172393749809,
      0.8110465113088715
    ],
    "page": "jiaocai_jiaocai_en_310",
    "order": 15
  },
  {
    "chunk_id": "docling_jiaocai_jiaocai_en_310_14",
    "text": "(i) ( ) Let H = {\"M\" \"w\" | TM M halts on input string wy, then H is NP-complete.",
    "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
